<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[189,303,267,293]" box="[189,303,267,293]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,267,293]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,267,293]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[189,1399,314,483]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
This species was originally described in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Moczar 1970 a)" baseAuthorityName="Moczar" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[676,1018,314,340]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Metrionotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[676,819,315,340]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Metrionotus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Moczar L." box="[836,1010,314,340]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="409 - 451" refId="ref7559" refString="Moczar L. 1970 a. Mesitiinae of world, genera Sulcomesitius Moczar and Metronotus Moczar. II. (Hymenoptera: Bethylidae). Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae 16: 409 - 451." type="journal article" year="1970">Móczár 1970a</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<collectingCountry box="[1139,1398,314,340]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">United Arab Emirates</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Barbosa D. N. &amp; Azevedo C. O." box="[197,517,350,376]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="375 - 404" refId="ref7132" refString="Barbosa D. N. &amp; Azevedo C. O. 2011 Order Hymenoptera, family Bethylidae, subfamily Mesitiinae. In: Harten A. van (ed.) Arthropod Fauna of UAE. Vol. 4: 375 - 404. Dar Al Ummah Printing, Publishing, Distribution &amp; Advertising, Abu Dhabi." type="journal article" year="2011">Barbosa &amp; Azevedo 2011</bibRefCitation>
). We examined one male type, the 
<typeStatus box="[957,1061,350,376]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">paratype</typeStatus>
, from material deposited at UFES, and the analyses reveal that its characteristics perfectly fit 
<taxonomicName authority="Barbosa &amp; Azevedo, 2019" authorityName="Barbosa &amp; Azevedo" authorityYear="2019" box="[991,1150,386,412]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Astromesitius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[991,1150,386,412]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Astromesitius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1160,1273,386,412]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, including the star-shaped hypopygium. Thus, we propose a new combination for this species from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moczar" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[1225,1368,422,447]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Metrionotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1225,1368,422,447]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Metrionotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authority="Barbosa &amp; Azevedo, 2019" authorityName="Barbosa &amp; Azevedo" authorityYear="2019" box="[189,348,457,483]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Astromesitius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,348,457,483]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Astromesitius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[355,462,457,483]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
